The '''''Encyclopedie van Friesland''''' is a [[Dutch language]] [[encyclopedia]] about the [[Friesland Province, Netherlands]] published in 1958 by [[Elsevier]].

In addition to an encyclopedic section, it consists of a compendium on, among other things, Frisian landscape,  the [[history of Friesland]], [[Frisian literature]] and [[Frisian culture]]. The editor-in-chief was [[J.H. Brouwer]]. He was assisted by an editorial board consisting of [[Jacob Kalma|J.J. Kalma]], [[W. Kok]] and [[M. Wiegersma]].

Post-1954 information was not included in the encyclopedia.
