'''''Słownik etymologiczny języka polskiego''''' (''Etymological Dictionary of the Polish Language'') is an [[etymological dictionary]] first published in 1927.  It was compiled by [[Aleksander Brückner]] and served through the 20th century as a principal [[Polish language|Polish]] etymological dictionary.  

Though now to some extent superseded by more recent efforts, it remains serviceable.

