{{More citations needed|date=January 2008}} {{Infobox website | name = Yahoo! Directory | logo = Yahoo Directory Logo 2013.png | logo_size = 90 | screenshot = | caption = | url = | commercial = | type = | registration = | owner = [[Yahoo!]] | author = | developer = | operating_system = | launch date = {{start date and age|1994|01}} | current status = Defunct as of December 26th 2014 | revenue = }}
The '''Yahoo! Directory''' was a [[web directory]] which at one time rivaled [[DMOZ]] in size. The directory was [[Yahoo!]]'s first offering and started in 1994 under the name '''Jerry and David's Guide to the World Wide Web'''.<ref>[https://www.golem.de/news/yahoo-directory-yahoo-schliesst-seinen-katalog-1409-109478.html Yahoo schließt seinen Katalog] from golem.de, September 27, 2014, retrieved in June 3, 2017</ref> When Yahoo! changed to [[Yahoo! Search|crawler-based listings]] for its main results in October 2002, the human-edited directory's significance dropped, but it was still being updated as of April 16, 2014.<ref>[http://dir.yahoo.com/new/20140416/regional/ Yahoo! Directory Additions for Wednesday April 16, 2014], Yahoo</ref> Users could browse thousands of listings which were organized in 7 or more tiers. For example, if a user was looking for a site on chess they might follow a path such as: recreation -> games -> board games -> chess.
The directory originally offered two options for suggesting websites for possible listing: "Standard", which was free,<ref name=How>[http://help.yahoo.com/l/us/yahoo/directory/listings/listings-03.html How do I add my site to the Yahoo! Directory?], Yahoo! website, accessed January 21, 2011</ref> and a paid submission process which offered expedited review.<ref>[https://ecom.yahoo.com/dir/submit/intro/ Yahoo! Directory Submit], Yahoo! website, accessed April 22, 2014</ref> "Standard" was dropped, and a non-refundable review fee of $299 ($600 for adult sites) was required when suggesting any website. If listed, the same amount was charged annually.
On September 26, 2014, Yahoo! announced that it would be closing the directory on December 31, 2014.<ref name=Closing>[http://yahoo.tumblr.com/post/98474044364/progress-report-continued-product-focus "Progress Report: Continued Product Focus"], Yahoo! September 26, 2014</ref> This followed the closing of a number of country-specific directories in 2010.<ref name=NoPlans>[http://searchengineland.com/yahoo-closes-european-directories-us-directory-safe-44610 "Yahoo! Closes European Directories, Says US Directory Is Safe"], SearchEngineLand.com, accessed August 13, 2010</ref>
